<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 4:29PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Roanoke,
southeastern Craig, west central Bedford, southwestern Botetourt and
northwestern Franklin Counties, the City of Salem and the City of
Roanoke through 500 PM EDT...
At 429 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Catawba, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Vinton...
Troutville...
Boones Mill...
Stewartsville...
and Montvale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
